CNCP v1 23431
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#7601: `v-model` on checkbox producing typing error when used with `true-value` and `false-value`",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:25:05.509710+00:00",
  "text": "`v-model` on checkbox producing typing error when used with `true-value` and `false-value`\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.2.45\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://sfc.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nFollowing the directions for [`true-value` and `false-value` checkboxes](https://vuejs.org/guide/essentials/forms.html#checkbox-1), the `v-model` property warns of an incorrect type.\n\n### What is expected?\n\nThe `true-value` and `false-value` property type should influence the expected types of the `v-model` property.\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nThe v-model property is restrict to https://github.com/vuejs/core/blob/e340add5a541df5d6563e24b11551b0d161d2f38/packages/runtime-dom/types/jsx.d.ts#L474\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nThis was first reported at https://github.com/johnsoncodehk/volar/issues/2341. The [suggested solution](https://github.com/johnsoncodehk/volar/issues/2341#issuecomment-1407601155) fixes the type error, however it then prevents utilising `const toggle` as a string in the script.",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: v-model"
  ],
